f the tail is defined, it could complicate things. I need to ensure `tailDefined` is true for the initial object too!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing stream behavior**\\n\\nI'm considering how `Stream(\\\"a\\\",\\\"b\\\")` behaves with tails. If the initial tail isn't defined, `writeReplace` might not return a proxy, leaving it uncovered. To ensure coverage, I might need to force `stream.tail` before serialization. This would lead to the proxy writing heads while the tail is defined. Once I write the first root, I have to check if the second stream defines its tail. Also, if I serialize the tail object, will `writeReplace` return it correctly? I think I should test for \\\"partially evaluated stream\\\" to assert lazy tail roundtrip.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering tail serialization**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the tail object that might include a lazy closure, which isn't serializable if it uses functions. So, I need to use a serializable tail. Perhaps a custom iterator could help avoid closures? In Scala, closures can be serializable, but is it safe for Native? To be cautious, I might prefer using a finite strict Stream. Using something like `val original = Stream(\\\"alpha\\\",\\\"beta\\\",\\\"gamma\\\"); original.tail` could guarantee that everything is defined. That sounds like a solid plan!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_DVfVs2G2pgNOCTAmxevtZf4a|fc_0a31162ad57974440169f5209123a88195870c7cebe6eef5dd", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.scala-lang/scala-library/2.11.8/src/test/scala/org_scala_lang/scala_library/TrieMapTest.scala"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 848, "output": 1082, "cacheRead": 22528, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24458, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777672317454, "responseId": "resp_0a31162ad57974440169f5207de56c81959a9be08c3c1456ff"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_DVfVs2G2pgNOCTAmxevtZf4a|fc_0a31162ad57974440169f5209123a88195870c7cebe6eef5dd", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_scala_lang.scala_library\n\nimport org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\n\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream\nimport java.io.ObjectInputStream\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream\nimport scala.collection.concurrent.TrieMap\nimport scala.math.Equiv\nimport scala.util.hashing.Hashing\n\nfinal class TrieMapTest {\n  @Test\n  def serializesAndRestoresEntriesThroughObjectStreams(): Unit = {\n    val original: TrieMap[String, Int] = newTrieMap()\n    original.put(\"alpha\", 1)\n    original.put(\"beta\", 2)\n    original.put(\"gamma\", 3)\n\n    val restored: TrieMap[String, Int] = deserializeTrieMap(serialize(original))\n\n    assertThat(restored).isNotSameAs(original)\n    assertThat(restored.size).isEqualTo(3)\n    assertThat(restored(\"alpha\")).isEqualTo(1)\n    assertThat(restored(\"beta\")).isEqualTo(2)\n    assertThat(restored(\"gamma\")).isEqualTo(3)\n    assertThat(restored.contains(\"missing\")).isFalse()\n  }\n\n  @Test\n  def deserializedTrieMapKeepsConcurrentMapMutationSemantics(): Unit = {\n    val original: TrieMap[String, Int] = newTrieMap()\n    original.update(\"initial\", 10)\n\n    val restored: TrieMap[String, Int] = deserializeTrieMap(serialize(original))\n    val previous: Option[Int] = restored.put(\"initial\", 11)\n    val inserted: Option[Int] = restored.putIfAbsent(\"new\", 12)\n    val removed: Option[Int] = restored.remove(\"initial\")\n\n    assertThat(previous.get).isEqualTo(10)\n    assertThat(inserted.isEmpty).isTrue()\n    assertThat(removed.get).isEqualTo(11)\n    assertThat(restored(\"new\")).isEqualTo(12)\n    assertThat(restored.contains(\"initial\")).isFalse()\n  }\n\n  private def newTrieMap(): TrieMap[String, Int] =\n    new TrieMap[String, Int](new TrieMapStringHashing(), new TrieMapStringEquiv())\n\n  private def serialize(map: TrieMap[String, Int]): Array[Byte] = {\n    val bytes: ByteArrayOutputStream = new ByteArrayOutputStream()\n    val out: ObjectOutputStream = new ObjectOutputStream(bytes)\n    try {\n      out.writeObject(map)\n      out.flush()\n      bytes.toByteArray\n    } finally {\n      out.close()\n    }\n  }\n\n  private def deserializeTrieMap(bytes: Array[Byte]): TrieMap[String, Int] = {\n    val in: ObjectInputStream = new ObjectInputStream(new ByteArrayInputStream(bytes))\n    try {\n      in.readObject().asInstanceOf[TrieMap[String, Int]]\n    } finally {\n      in.close()\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nfinal class TrieMapStringHashing extends Hashing[String] {\n  override def hash(value: String): Int = value.##\n}\n\nfinal class TrieMapStringEquiv extends Equiv[String] {\n  override def equiv(left: String, right: String): Boolean = left == right\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777672337465}]}
